      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "What you are describing sounds like deep depression or a complicated identity crisis, not simply moving on from sadness, and true help often involves acknowledging that grief for yourself matters just as much as grief for someone else. While the feeling that your \"real life\" died sounds permanent, clinical support can sometimes reveal that this is a surviving part of you engaging with overwhelming pain rather than an actual end to who you are. Please consider speaking with a mental health professional who can help untangle these overwhelming thoughts from reality, as you do not have to navigate this shell alone.",
      "source": "target",
